		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>It seems to me like I am the only character that is not twinked.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a 20 monk, that's kind of rough, because warriors are wanted for groups more. They can take more, hand out more, and taunt.  Wizards complain I don't do enough damage when they are aggro'd by red "bad guys."  And with a complete lack of any kind of monk weapon that I could feasibly get, all my weapon skills have fallen behind.  Is there any kind of quest or way I can get some sort equipment to help me? whether it adds AC or damage, I just don't seem to measure up in any department.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Mar 26th 7:36 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=9856347181551&num=1&page=&post=1&replyto=9856534122892"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9856534122892></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Monks are probably one of the more powerful damage dishers in the game at high levels. True, you will never raise any eyebrows, partly because your damage is comparable to a DOT...small amounts over a period of time, but it happens very fast. When a warrior is hitting one time for 50, you will kick,punch,eagle strike for 10,18,15 in that amount of time. Now to the meat of the matter.....<br><br>There is no better pulling class than a MONK...FD allows you to run into any dungeon safely (assuming your skill is high) pull multiple mobs back to your group, and FD, allowing the warrior to pull one at a time with an arrow while the others have peeled off. Only a monk can do this successfully time after time. this is especially helpful if you do not have an enchanter in your group.<br><br>Don't worry so much about your hand to hand and various combat skills, they will go up, as that is all you have to work with...just keep practicing all of them. For training at your guild, I would suggest putting almost all of your points into FD and the rest into mend...FD is what makes monks so handy. Don't be too concerned with wizards and mags telling you that you arent doing enough damage, if they knew how to play their class, they wouldnt be nuking until the end of the fight anyways, when they are supposed to. When you hit level 46, you will be needed WAY over nukers in the planes. TANKS, CLERICS, and CHANTERS are the three main classes for raids....MONK = TANK, bigtime!! <br><br>If you were on the same server (Zebuxoruk)as me, I will readily make you some cured silk armor (AC), or even take you to Dalnir and get some crescent armor, mighty fine armor for a monk. Both are relatively easy, but the crescent armor is damn fine stuff. Hope this helps, and don't get down on your monk, I dont play one, but it is a class I've always admired and sought for when grouping.<br><br>Kannayyan 56 necro<br>Demetre 31 SK<br>Aristotl 29 cleric<br>Starri 34 druid<br><br>Zebuxoruk Server<br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
